# Multi-Agent Algorithmic Backtesting & Risk Engine

An enterprise-grade, event-driven full-stack application designed to ingest natural language trading strategies, parse core parameters via an asynchronous AI agent orchestration layer, and execute deterministic mathematical backtests against historical market asset data.

## System Architecture & Data Flow

```text
[Client Interface: React JS] 
       │ (HTTP POST Payload: Ticker & Strategy Prompt)
       ▼
[API Gateway: FastAPI Server]
       │
       ├─► [AI Intelligence Layer: OpenAI GPT Pipeline]
       │     └─ Synthesizes raw prompt text into intent structures
       │
       └─► [Execution Analytics Engine: Pandas & YFinance]
             └─ Ingests historical market data arrays and runs moving averages
       │
       ▼
[Unified JSON Return Object] ──► Rendered on Client Dashboard


Client Ingestion: The React frontend captures user-defined strategy concepts and asset tickers, dispatching an optimized JSON payload to the REST backend.

AI Semantic Parsing: The FastAPI service handles the request, consulting an isolated AI Agent configuration layer to analyze conceptual strategy parameters and risk paradigms.

Deterministic Core: Concurrently, the execution data engine interfaces with public market infrastructure APIs (yfinance), mapping price action data arrays into local Pandas DataFrames to calculate 20-day and 50-day crossing moving averages.

State Convergence: Financial computations and semantic AI insights converge into a standardized response schema returned to the client at sub-second latencies.

Core Tech Stack
Frontend UI: React JS, Client-Side State Hooks, Lucide Vector Icons

Application Server: FastAPI (Python), Uvicorn ASGI Web Server, Pydantic Data Validation

Data Processing: Pandas DataFrames, Yahoo Finance Analytical Client API

Cognitive Compute: OpenAI API Engine Wrapper

Production Local Deployment Setup
1. Backend Service Initialization
Bash
cd backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
2. Frontend Client Initialization
Bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev

